<li>Schwarz, J.-O. (2008) <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://linkinghub.elsevier.com/retrieve/pii/S0016328707001073">Assessing the future of futures studies in management</a>, Futures, Vol. 40, Iss. 3, 237-246.</li>
<li>Shakhnazarov, G. K. (1982). Futurology fiasco: a critical study of non-Marxist concepts of how society develops. Moscow: Progress Publishers.</li>
<li>Slaughter, Richard A. (1995), <i>Futures for the Third Millennium</i>. Prospect Media, St. Leonards, NSW, Australia, <a href="Special_BookSources/1863161481" class="internal mw-magiclink-isbn">ISBN 1-86316-148-1</a>.</li>
<li>Slaughter, Richard A. (2004), <i>Futures Beyond Dystopia: Creating Social Foresight</i>. RoutledgeFarmer, London, UK, <a href="Special_BookSources/9780415302708" class="internal mw-magiclink-isbn">ISBN 978-0-415-30270-8</a></li>
<li>Slaughter, Richard A. (2005). <i>The Knowledge Base of Futures Studies Professional Edition CDROM.</i> Foresight International, Indooroopilly, Australia</li>
<li>Thompson, A. E. (1979). <i>Understanding futurology: an introduction to futures study.</i> Newton Abbot [Eng.]: David &amp; Charles.</li>
<li>Woodgate, Derek with Pethrick, Wayne R. (2004). <i>Future Frequencies.</i> Fringecore, Austin, Texas, USA</li>
</ul>
